  "body": "It seems like Remix includes the metadata hash in the compilation of the contracts. This can lead to various confusing outcomes, such as the one described in https://github.com/ethereum/remix-project/issues/293.\r\n\r\nIt would be nice if we could disable the metadata hash via a check box. Most development frameworks offer this feature today, e.g. this is how I do it in Hardhat:\r\n\r\nhttps://github.com/paulrberg/solidity-template/blob/2de6b59757e0dd7f467d7549074329391a5d671f/hardhat.config.ts#L83",
